 to start the server. The public API path, like `org.apache.catalina.connector.Connector.getProperty`, seems ideal for testing reflection without port issues. Starting Tomcat tests type reachability, but I want to ensure I'm only testing the Connector's reachability and not editing any metadata. It might be helpful to refine the existing test to call properties on a started connector, as this setup already accounts for configuration and assertions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing runtime issues**\\n\\nI’m noticing that `getName` returns \\\"http-nio-8080\\\" before the server starts, and SSLEnabled is false, but it seems like `getProperty` might be returning null, which is meaningful in context. This issue might relate to the Latest Spring Petclinic failing at runtime since Tomcat is using reflective introspection on protocol methods. It’s possible Spring Boot relies on some form of introspection only after the connector starts, which could explain the failure. I need to investigate this further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_uqTL2bZspUN8iuN1lAq79isu|fc_020c30035824428e016a0df99061e08191b06cec16e21d96f0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/main/extracted/org/apache/catalina/connector/Connector.java", "offset": 930, "limit": 180}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/main/extracted/org/apache/catalina/connector/Connector.java\",\"offset\":930,\"limit\":180}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 457, "output": 993, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27562, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779300736556, "responseId": "res